# Priority Pass restaurant

Good thing Robert reminded me of this before the trip\. The one line in PDX was closed to priority pass when I arrived so I detoured to the available Cafe and got a good meal for the cost of a few spare bucks in tip\. 

Did eventually get into the lounge and it was lousy with amenities\. Previewing what's available in Narita and I'm starting to think that Hanoi and Taipei fucked my expectations curve

entries.text:
# Jetlag

There's something so odd about spending all day on a plane and them just wanting to lay down and sleep\. Like, I didn't expend any energy\. 

Though in this case it makes sense because I didn't nap on the flight and Seattle time it's 1am and I awoke at 5:30 on little sleep\.

I think if I could make it to like 8pm before crashing that'd be good but I'm trying not to force anything\. It'd feel accomplishing to get the Tokyo stuff done but ehhhh, see how I feel after a shower\. And also where I need to go tomorrow to get rail pass and Hiroshima train\.

Tokyo Stuff
- Owl Cafe
- Godzilla
- Ghibli clock
- Rainbow bridge

Ended up with decent initial energy burst\. Walked through the shrine I ended my trip with last time \(makes sense\) and browsed the blossoms along Sumida Park\. Then got Lawson's takeaway and now back to sleep\.

entries.text:
# Travel thoughts on the ground

Some random thoughts on travel planning: I may be getting better at allowing myself freedom to just be in a place, but one thing this first morning in Japan has reminded me of is that I like to have the first few steps of the day already researched\. That way I can relax into the day and not wake up and immediately feel like I'm behind schedule or that I don't know what I'm doing / when to get out of bed / etc\.

Tokyo to Hiroshima to Kyoto is the example here\. I knew that's what I wanted to do, but didn't have any other plan other than knowing that roughly that was doable\.

I woke up this morning and had to figure out:
\- Which train station in Tokyo I was going to\.
\- When the JR Pass office opened
\- The bullet train timetable to Hiroshima
\- Based on that, when I had to leave the hostel this morning
\- The check\-in times for my hostel in Kyoto

It can be as simple as here's the opening times of a few things, or the transit timetable\. But, like, have the day until 10am semi\-figured out\.

# Bizarre OH conversation

Retired women seemingly booking long cruises on a whim\. Iceland plus Greenland\. Spend lots of time traveling, recounting recent trips\. Seem Indian?

Then mention they like taking local buses on the cruise stops because the official activities are too expensive\. Can't tell if these are my dream future selves or rich soiled people\.

Just mildly stressful that I'll be putting my eggs in the last two days basket since Osaka and Kyoto don't enter full bloom until Thursday by current expectation and Thur/Fri are my Nagano days."}]}
entries.text:
# A few days early o\. Timing

Mild irritating that blossoms got delayed a few days in Osaka and Kyoto\. I was all set to be literally perfectly timed and then a couple days set things slightly awry\. Will try to adjust\. Do want to catch at least one full bloom somewhere\. Fall back is Tokyo\.

Just mildly stressful that I'll be putting my eggs in the last two days basket since Osaka and Kyoto don't enter full bloom until Thursday by current expectation and Thur/Fri are my Nagano days\.
